# RBAC in UI

## Use workspace permissions

```tsx
import { usePermissions, usePermission } from '@/context/PermissionsContext';

const { can } = usePermissions();
const canDelete = usePermission('products.delete');
```

Permission keys: `src/server/constants/permissionCatalog.ts`

## Rules

- Hide destructive/export buttons when `!can('key')` — do not rely on PIN alone
- PIN supplements RBAC for floor staff; it does not replace missing permissions
- Do not use `user?.isAdmin` for access control (OK for PIN bypass display only)
- Gate handlers: early-return if `!can('key')` even when button is hidden

## Route-level

Main modules should match `SIDEBAR_PERMISSIONS` via `ProtectedRoute permission="..."`.
`PermissionsProvider` must wrap permission checks in `App.tsx`.
